data.name: [BEST OF CITY] Styleguide
data.description:
Craig needs a styleguide to instruct the conversion house as to how to manually create a best of city guide. Most can be copied and pasted from the country guide, in fact you probably don't even need to update the screenshots - they're enough to get the message across. We just need the city specific chapters added to the guide (see below).

You might need to re order the chapters a little as they differ in city guides

As for the points you need to document - see the country doc (https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B4T3EZVPqm4TMmN6NDBUdnVWTDA) for examples. It's good to specify colour hexes, but you don't need to go overboard, the sample epub we'll provide them will give them the detail - this is a high level type of thing.

DEADLINES/requirements: Draft of City Instructions doc to Craig by Friday 24 June.  He wants to send it to India by the following Friday 1 July.  He doesn't need a full book sample epub, so we can build screenshots for city-specific sections from existing chapter exports.

#318/#78 [EBOOKS] Pocket: Ensure standalone/Worth a Trip Top Sights come through in TOC (eg Pudu, Ampang, Batu, Frim in Pocket KL)
data.description:
https://github.com/lonelyplanet/remixer/issues/318
https://github.com/lonelyplanet/ebooks-assets/issues/78

You want something like in the pocket table of contents stylesheet: app/generators/compilers/epub/toc/pocket/stylesheet.rb: 

````
render '.standalone-local-life h2',    with: :doc_link
render '.standalone.top-sights h2',    with: :doc_link
````


and another pocket exceptional rule for the machine table of contents: in app/generators/compilers/epub/ncx/stylesheet.rb


````
render '.pocket.explore .standalone-local-life h2',  with: :navpoint
render '.pocket.explore .standalone.top-sights h2',  with: :navpoint
````

^^ Comes completely without warranty and untested - don't forget the specs (spec/generators/compilers/epub/toc/pocket_spec.rb and spec/generators/compilers/epub/ncx/stylesheet_spec.rb) enjoy!

[CHRISTO] [FILTERS] Regression: the orange bolding/highlighting on Place names in the CMS Place menu doesn't reflect search criteria.
data.description:
**Blocked on 1737**

The orange highlighting on Place names in the CMS Place menu doesn't reflect search criteria.

Place names should highlight where contained narrative and/or POIs matches current filter.


Steps to reproduce:

1. (under the #filter_panel switch) Load a place with subplaces

2. Enter a (fairly broad) search term into the CMS Keyword search field

3. = all loaded Places that contain content (narrative or POIs) relevant to the search should appear in bold and orange in the CMS Place list.  This is not happening.  It looks to me like the bold/orange might only be being applied to Places that have a *POI* that fits the search criteria.  

check out the attached video.
